## Questions people often ask

{% accordion_group %}
{% accordion question="Do I need a finished brief?" %}
No. A useful starting point is enough. We can shape the brief once the context and priorities are clearer.
{% /accordion %}
{% accordion question="Do I need to know the exact deliverables?" %}
No. We can work out whether the answer is a brand, publication, campaign, website, interface or a combination of things.
{% /accordion %}
{% accordion question="What if my budget is still being worked out?" %}
Say so. A candid conversation lets us explore a sensible scope and avoid pretending that every idea needs to happen at once.
{% /accordion %}
{% accordion question="Can I bring rough references or notes?" %}
Absolutely. Rough material often helps reveal the tone, audience or problem faster than a polished document.
{% /accordion %}
{% accordion question="What happens after the first conversation?" %}
I will help turn what we have discussed into a clear next step, whether that is a proposal, a focused workshop or more preparation.
{% /accordion %}
{% /accordion_group %}

